Changes in version 1.30:

-Added wav2cd utility . This one allows you to make an audio cd
from all the wave files found in the current directory .

- Added the -t parameter to all writing utilities
to perform write operation in test mode .

- Fixed a bug in daocopy that did not work when
started from the root directory of the hard drive .


Changes in version 1.20:

- cdrecord2 and cdrtools2 are now fully useable .

- Improved CDRCHECK program .

- Sources now provided .


Changes in version 1.10:

- Now can run under 4OS2 command processor (thanks to Duane Chamblee) .

- Added the -horm flag to clip2cd and daocopy
allowing to normalize tracks level .
You can get the normalize package from hobbes .
